    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="591" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 8,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Said Pasha, former foreign minister, reappointed. Consul of the United
                            States at Beirut reports activity of revolutionary leaders in interior,
                            and that missionaries dread being assassinated by revolutionists, who
                            hope thus to bring odium on the Turks. They also fear massacre by the
                            Turks. My demand for orders to all civil and military chiefs in all
                            provinces for protection of Americans has been renewed. Still dread the
                            effect of recent events here on remote provinces. * * * The Armenian
                            churches have been filled for a week by Armenians who refuse to leave,
                            whether from apprehension or because revolutionary leaders require it as
                            an object lesson to influence Christian powers, opinions differ. Order
                            seems restored, but all Armenian business houses are closed under
                            instructions from Armenian committee.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
